On May 28, the student who had protested in the cafeteria of Xi'an Translation Institute in March was punished by the school for violation of discipline two months later
Previous situation: On March 3, some netizens revealed that Xi'an Translation Institute still had a semi-closed management model, which caused dissatisfaction among students and they protested on social platforms such as Weibo.
On March 7, the school announced that it would cancel the measures and open the dormitories, but it was not implemented on March 8, resulting in multiple conflicts in the school that day. Among them, the student's speech in the cafeteria became the climax of the day and was widely circulated inside and outside the wall.
